About Me

From an early age I was inspired by the world of Interiors and after graduating from Bucks University with a degree in Textiles and Surface Design I knew that Interior Design was the career for me.

​

After university I worked for reputable design brands such as Laura Ashley and Evitavonni before landing my very first interior design role. I worked within the show home industry for over 5 years, specialising in turning blank spaces into beautiful aspirational homes – who doesn’t want to own a show home. I have experience working with different shaped/sized houses from 1-bedroom flats to large family homes all over the UK and I am very familiar with that overwhelming feeling of a blank canvas and where to start.

​

In 2018 I graduated from Jo Chrobak’s Interior Design Business School. This is when I decided to pursue my dreams of owning my very own design service and launched Amy Elizabeth Interiors. I now have over 10 years experience working in the industry.

"Live in a home you love."
